<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>President Donald Trump confirmed on Wednesday that another White House staffer has tested positive for the coronavirus.</p>

<p>'It's not anybody that was near me,' he said at his press conference.</p>

<p>White House press secretary Kayleigh McEnany stepped in to say the person will not be identified and it did not affect any events around the White House.</p>

<p>'We're not going to confirm the identity of the individual. It did not affect the event and press was not around,' she said.</p>

<p>It was not immediately clear what event she was referring to. </p>

<p>President Donald Trump confirmed that another White House staffer has tested positive for the coronavirus</p>

<p>White House press secretary Kayleigh McEnany stepped in to say the person will not be identified and it did not affect any events around the White House</p>

<p>The White House held a signing ceremony on Wednesday for its deal between Israel, the UAE and Bahrain. The president also attended a town hall meeting in Philadelphia on Wednesday night.  </p>

<p>Senior White House staff and the president receive COVID tests daily.  </p>

<p>Additionally anyone meeting with the president or getting near him is tested for the virus. </p>
